# Documentation Rules

Documentation is part of the product system, but Vault Markdown is the source of truth.

## README

- Keep the top-level README useful as the project entry point.
- Include the project structure, setup hints, and links to durable rules.
- Preserve existing useful setup notes when updating the README.

## Vault Specs

- Follow the Vault First rules in `01-obsidian.mdc`.
- Treat Vault Markdown as the source of truth for long-lived specifications, decisions, knowledge, project state, and task state.
- Keep implementation synchronized with Vault notes when behavior changes.

## Style

- Prefer concise Markdown with stable headings.
- Use checklists for concrete work.
- Use diagrams when structure is easier to understand visually.
- Avoid duplicating Vault operating rules outside `01-obsidian.mdc`; link to that rule instead.
